---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy | One Less Thing"
  description="One Less Thing's privacy policy. We collect minimal data, don't sell it, and try to be straightforward about what we do."
>

  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container--narrow">
      <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        We collect as little data as possible and don't sell any of it.
        Here's the full picture.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container--narrow page-body">

    <p class="meta">Last updated: May 6, 2026 &middot; Questions? <a href="mailto:hayden@onelessthing.us">hayden@onelessthing.us</a></p>

    <section aria-labelledby="who-heading">
      <h2 id="who-heading">Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        One Less Thing Inc. is a Nebraska-based disability financial literacy company.
        This policy applies to the website onelessthing.us and our newsletter.
        We are the data controller for information collected through these services.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="collect-heading">
      <h2 id="collect-heading">What we collect</h2>

      <h3>Newsletter subscribers</h3>
      <p>
        If you sign up for our newsletter, we collect your email address. Our newsletter
        is hosted by Beehiiv. When you subscribe, your email is stored in Beehiiv's systems
        and subject to <a href="https://www.beehiiv.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">their privacy policy</a>.
        We use your email only to send you the newsletter. We will never sell it or share it
        with third-party advertisers.
      </p>

      <h3>Website analytics</h3>
      <p>
        We use basic, privacy-focused analytics to understand how people use the site —
        things like which pages are visited and roughly where traffic comes from.
        We do not use tracking cookies for advertising purposes.
        We do not build profiles of individual visitors.
      </p>

      <h3>Contact email</h3>
      <p>
        If you email us directly, we receive your email address and the content of your message.
        We use this only to respond to you. We do not add you to any mailing list without your consent.
      </p>

      <h3>What we don't collect</h3>
      <p>
        We do not collect Social Security numbers, financial account numbers, medical records,
        or any other sensitive personal or financial data. This is a content and newsletter site —
        there is no account system and no financial transactions.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="use-heading">
      <h2 id="use-heading">How we use your information</h2>
      <p>We use data we collect to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Send the newsletter to people who signed up for it.</li>
        <li>Respond to messages you send us.</li>
        <li>Understand how the site is used so we can improve it.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not use your data for advertising, profiling, or any automated decision-making.</p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="share-heading">
      <h2 id="share-heading">Who we share data with</h2>
      <p>We use the following third-party services:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Beehiiv</strong> — Newsletter hosting. Stores subscriber email addresses.
          <a href="https://www.beehiiv.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy policy</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>GitHub Pages</strong> — Website hosting. May log standard server access data
          (IP addresses, browser type). <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy policy</a>.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not sell, rent, or trade your information to any third party.
        We will disclose information if required by law.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="retain-heading">
      <h2 id="retain-heading">How long we keep data</h2>
      <p>
        Newsletter subscriber data is retained until you unsubscribe.
        Every newsletter includes an unsubscribe link. You can also email us directly
        to be removed: <a href="mailto:hayden@onelessthing.us">hayden@onelessthing.us</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Email correspondence is retained only as long as needed to resolve your inquiry.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="rights-heading">
      <h2 id="rights-heading">Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live, you may have the right to access, correct, or delete
        information we hold about you. To make a request, email
        <a href="mailto:hayden@onelessthing.us">hayden@onelessthing.us</a>.
        We will respond within 30 days.
      </p>
      <p>
        Nebraska residents: this policy is consistent with Nebraska data protection practices.
        If you have questions about your rights under Nebraska law, please contact us.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="children-heading">
      <h2 id="children-heading">Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>
        This site is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect
        personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us
        with information, contact us and we will delete it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="changes-heading">
      <h2 id="changes-heading">Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        If we make material changes to this policy, we will post the updated version here
        and update the "last updated" date. We won't notify newsletter subscribers of
        routine updates, but we will notify you of significant changes that affect how
        we use your data.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="contact-heading">
      <h2 id="contact-heading">Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy or your data? Email
        <a href="mailto:hayden@onelessthing.us">hayden@onelessthing.us</a>.
        We are a small team and will respond personally.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="disclaimer" role="note">
      <p>
        <em>This content is for educational purposes only and does not constitute legal, tax,
        or financial advice. Consult a qualified professional for your specific situation.</em>
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-header {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 3rem 0 2.5rem;
  }
  .page-header h1 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .lead { font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-body); }
  .page-body { padding: 3rem 1.5rem; }
  .meta { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .page-body section { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .page-body h2 { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .page-body h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1rem; }
  .page-body ul { padding-left: 1.25rem; }
  .page-body li { margin-bottom: 0.6rem; line-height: 1.6; }
  .page-body p { margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .disclaimer {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-md) var(--radius-md) 0;
  }
  .disclaimer p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-muted); }
</style>
